select count(*) as aggregate from (select GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.id) as id, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.title) as title, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.permalink) as permalink, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.page_image) as page_image, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.visibility) as visibility, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.parent) as parent, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.publish_at) as publish_at, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.is_home) as is_home, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.page_type) as page_type, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.publish_status) as publish_status, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_pages.updated_at) as updated_at, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_users.id) as user_id, GROUP_CONCAT(distinct tl_users.name) as user_name from `tl_pages` inner join `tl_users` on `tl_users`.`id` = `tl_pages`.`user_id` left join `tl_page_templates` on `tl_page_templates`.`id` = `tl_pages`.`page_template` where (`tl_pages`.`publish_status` != '3') and (`tl_pages`.`title` like '%%' or `tl_pages`.`visibility` like '%%' or `tl_pages`.`content` like '%%' or `tl_users`.`name` like '%%') group by `tl_pages`.`id`) as `aggregate_table`
